  saturated fat: 22 g
  carbohydrates: 103 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 1650 mg
cuisine: Indian
course: main course
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/coconut-curry-shrimp-with-chickpeas-64dd0857ef3d37ebd500fff4
author: HelloFresh
time required: 30 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}(minced). Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}(finely diced). Core, deseed, and finely dice @bell pepper{1}(finely diced). Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%can}. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped).

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and bell pepper; cook until softened and lightly browned, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir in @tomato paste{1%unit}, @curry powder{1%tbsp}, @paprika{1%tsp}, half the @garam masala{1%tsp}, and remaining garlic until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

> Love the earthy warmth of garam masala? Add more if you like!

Stir in chickpeas, @coconut milk{1%unit}, @veggie stock concentrate{1%unit}, 1/4 cup water, and @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to low; cook until thickened, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> If curry seems too thick, stir in a splash of water.

Remove from heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Rinse @shrimp{10%oz} under cold water. Pat shrimp dry with #paper towels{}; season with salt and pepper. Add to pan along with onion. Cook, stirring occasionally, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with curry. Dollop with @yogurt{2%tbsp}. Garnish with cilantro and serve.